Company Description: Founded IN 1991, Particle Sciences Is An Integrated Provider Of Both Standard And Nanotechnology Approaches To Drug Development And Delivery. The Company Originally Pioneered Use Of Encapsulated Ingredients And Nanoparticles For Sunscreens And Personal Care. IN 1999 The Company Licensed A Portion Of Its Nanotechnology Portfolio To Basf And Focused Its Efforts On Providing Services To Life Sciences Companies. Now, Through A Full Range Of Formulation, Analytic, And Manufacturing Services, Particle Sciences Provides Pharmaceutical Companies With A Complete And Seamless Development Solution Designed To Minimize The Time And Risk Between Discovery And The Clinic. With A Comprehensive Formulations Laboratory, State-Of-The-Art Physical Characterization Methodologies, A Cgmp Analytical Laboratory And Clean Room Facilities, Particle Sciences Can Help You Build Your Discovery Into A Product. We Have Experience IN A Number Of Formats Including Gels, Emulsions, Suspensions, Solutions, Particulates And Drug/Device Combination Products. Particle Sciences Has Specialized Capabilities IN Topical And Mucosal Drug Delivery With Additional Experience IN Parenteral And Oral Formulations. Particle Sciences Difference Unique Specialization. Fine-Particle And Nanoscale Systems Have Been A Focus Of Particle Sciences Since Its Inception IN 1991. Our Staff Has Extensive Experience IN The Areas Of Particulates, Emulsions, Suspensions, Micronization, Encapsulation And Drug Delivery. Particle Sciences Has All The Necessary Instrumentation And IN-House Expertise To Produce And Characterize These Systems. Working With Multiple Delivery Formats, We Offer Unique Expertise IN Topical And Mucosal Therapeutics. Exceptional Staff. Our Talented Staff Come From A Variety Of Backgrounds And Includes Physicians, Engineers, And Doctorate-Level Surface, Analytic, Material Science And Polymer Chemists. Combined, The Senior Management Particle Sciences Has Well Over 100 Years Experience IN Drug Development And Innovation. Integrated Process. Through A Combination Of Preformulation, Formulation, Analytic And Manufacturing Services, Particle Sciences Provides Clients With A Powerful, Integrated Solution To Most Efficiently Take A Drug From Discovery To The Clinic. Each Project Has A Dedicated Team And Leader To Manage The Project From Start To Finish. Creative. To Ensure Successful Drug Development, Particle Sciences Blends Creativity With Experience To Arrive At The Simplest, Most Efficient Solution To The Client's Needs. Problem-Solving. With Years Of Experience To Draw From, Particle Sciences Can Confidently Handle Difficult Apis, Complicated Intellectual Property Terrains And Challenging Delivery Goals. Efficient. Clients With Demanding Performance Requirements And Timelines Will Benefit From The Speed, Efficiency And Quality That Particle Sciences Delivers. Collaborative. Particle Sciences Maintains An 'open Door Policy' With Its Clients And Provides Ready Access To Lab Facilities And Staff. Clients Can Consider Particle Sciences An Expert Extension Of Their IN-House Development Team. Client-Focused. Client's Projects Receive Individualized Attention. Particle Sciences Prefers To Take A Consultative Approach To Ensure Positive Project Outcomes And The Highest Levels Of Client Satisfaction. Projects Are Overseen And Coordinated By A Dedicated Project Manager IN Conjunction With A Cross-Functional Team.

Company Description: The Purolite Company Is Dedicated To The Development Of Ion Exchange Resins, Adsorbents And Polymeric Catalysts. With Manufacturing, Warehousing, Application And Research Facilities Throughout The World, The Company Is Not Only One Of The Largest Manufacturers Of Ion Exchange Resins IN The World, But Also One Of The Fastest Growing. The Primary Applications For Ion Exchange Resins Are Industrial Water Treatment, Softening, Dealkalization And Demineralization. Purolite Offers More Than 400 Products. It Manufactures Products That Are Widely Used IN The Manufacture Of Pharmaceuticals; Electronics, Where Its Low Total Organic Carbon Resins Meet The Demand For Ultra-Pure Water For Manufacturing Semiconductors; The Chemical And Refining Industries, Where The Company Helps Its Customers Produce Essential Products, While Minimizing Their Environmental Impact; And IN The Food Industry For Manufacturing Items Such As Sweeteners, Dairy Products, Fruit Juices And Gelatin. Company Description: Selecting A Qualified Electrical Contractor For Your Home OR Business Can Be Challenging. It's A Little Like Taking Your Car Into A Car Dealer OR Going To The Doctor. You Know Something Is Wrong, But You Lack The Expertise To Diagnose The Problem Yourself And You Are At The Mercy Of The Supposed Expert. You Also Might Have Difficulty Describing Your Problem Completely, OR Be Confused By The Jargon Used By The Professionals. We Can't Help You With The Auto Mechanic OR The Doctor, But We Would Like To Take A Little Of The Mystery Out Of Selecting And Dealing With Electrical Contractors.Most Electrical Contractors Are Specialists To One Degree OR Another, So It Helps To Identify Your Particular Need Before You Start Calling. Is Your Need For New Construction OR Major Renovation? Are You Looking For Service OR Repair Of Existing Electrical Items? Is The Work Needed For Your Home, A Small Business, OR A Major Facility? Does This Need Represent An Emergency, OR Are You Concerned About A Dangerous Condition That Exists? Does Your Work Include Specialized Systems, Such As Fire Alarm, Security, Sound, Video, Communications, Wired OR Wireless Networks? Answering A Few Of These Questions, At Least IN Your Own Mind, Will Help You First To Select A Qualified Contractor, And Then To Describe Your Electrical Needs To The Person That You Call.Once You Have Defined Your Specific Need, Your Goals Are To Find A Contractor That Is:*technically Proficient,*reputable And Financially Stable, And*has A Thorough Understanding Of Your Business.

Company Description: Rutgers Organics Corporation, Founded IN 1951 As The Pedlow Nease Company, Is A Supplier Of Specialty Chemicals And Custom Manufacturing Services. The Company Also Operates A Warehouse And Service Center For A Line Of Fine Chemicals And Organic Intermediates Produced IN Germany By The Rutgers Organics Division And Sold IN The United States. Principal Markets For These Imports Include The Pharmaceutical, Personal Care, Pigment, Polymer, And Graphics Industries. Rutgers Organics Features A Complete Line Of Hydrotopes IN Composition And Form On The Market. Sold Under The Naxonate Trademark, These Alkylarylsulfonates Find Their Greatest Utility IN Laundry And Dishwashing Detergents, Where The Hydrotope's Coupling Action Stabilizes Consumer Product Formulations. Additional Applications Are IN Industrial And Institutional Cleaners, Electroplating Agents, Adhesives, Textile Specialties And Other Products. The Company Also Markets A Specialty Surfactant Line, Which Includes Phosphate Esters, Linear Alkyl Sulfonates, Alkanolamides, And Powdered Sulfates. With Applications From Personal Care To Emulsion Polymerization To Metal Working Fluids, These Surface-Active Agents Are Essential Ingredients IN Many Formulations.

Company Description: Tasty Baking Company S History Goes Back To 1914, When A Pittsburgh Baker, Philip J. Baur, And A Boston Egg Salesman, Herbert T. Morris, Went Into Business To Produce Baked Goods. They Insisted On Farm Fresh Eggs, Grade A Creamery Butter, Real Milk, Cocoa, Spices And Natural Flavorings. Morris  Wife Said The First Cakes Baked Were  Tasty , So Morris And Baur Named The Business Tasty Baking Company And Came Up With The Catchy Name, Tastykake, For Its Products. At Ten Cents A Cake, Morris Sold More Than $220 Worth IN The First Week. By The End Of 1914, Gross Sales Were Nearly $300,000. Other Products Include Cupcakes, Donuts, Honey Buns, Juniors, Kandy Kakes, Kremies, Krimpets, Pies, Sensables, Snak Bars, Seasonal Items And Snowballs. With More Than $250 Million IN Annual Sales, Tasty Baking Company Has A Location IN Philadelphia.

Univar Was Founded As A Brokerage When Founders George Van Waters And Nat Rogers Started Buying And Selling Naval Stores, Paint, Raw Materials And Cotton Linters IN The Pacific Northwest. The Company Eventually Moved Into The Chemical Distribution Business And Grew Throughout The West And Into The Eastern United States. Univar Entered The Canadian Market IN 1950 And Europe IN 1991. Univar Usa Is The Company S Chemical Distribution Subsidiary IN The United States. IN Canada, Operations Are Known As Univar Canada. Operating IN 14 Countries Throughout Europe, The Company Is Known As Univar Europe. Its Parent Company, Univar, Is A Dutch Company Listed On The Euronext Amsterdam Stock Exchange As Univr.
